<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10279920054641></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10279920054641><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10279920054641>Sounds confused</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10279920054641#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73409><span id=Scholar>Mistress ancarett</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 29th 9:33 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.57]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There's a similar tactic that shamans use by recasting inner fire (low level buff) for the heal potential.<br><br>But if your target already has symbol on them, you're not going to get a hit point increase beyond the max. So that shouldn't work with symbol (not to mention the reagent cost, eek).<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>-- Yseulte/Ancarett<br>Veeshan Server</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
