<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10280276943768></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10280276943768><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10280276943768>RE: Sounds confused</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10280276943768#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153318><span id=Scholar>Nrewfin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>15 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 30th 7:14 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can use your buffs to heal as opposed to actual heal spells, but symbol is not the one you would use.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your HP / AC buffs increase hitpoints when they are cast, and then once that spell is already on your target and is cast again, their HP is again raised by total amount of HP for that spell (hope that made sense).  For example, Daring adds a maximum 115hp's.  If you are casting Daring on your target and he has 700/900hp's, his HPs will go up to 815/1015.  Then, when casting Daring on your target a 2nd time, his HP's will go up to 930/1015.  Healing with this line of spells is an excellent way to raise your abjuration skill.  When I was in my 20's-30's, my skill was very low level and I was told to heal using these spells.  Its quite effective for smaller heals, especially on casters.  If you are going to use this on your main melee who is taking a lot of damage, use when they have a lot of hp left, 115hp's to a big warrior won't do much, but could be enough to save his life if you don't have mana or casting time for one of your heals.  Here is a list of the line of spell buffs that you are able to heal with:<br><br>Courage (L1), Center(L9), Daring(L19), Bravery(L24), Valor(L34){right click effect on Donal's Arms}, Resolution(L44), Heroism / Heroic Bond (Group Version of Heroism)(L52), and Fortitude (L55).<br><br>Nrewfin Givinglife<br>55th Templar of Brell<br>Accursed Divinity<br>The Seventh Hammer<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
